I enjoyed the gameplay, and would have given a 5/5 for gameplay alone. However, the ads in the game are excessive, appearing after almost every stage, and all to get you to subscribe. The rate for subscription is $8 a week, which feels outrageous for a supposedly free app! If an upfront payment option is added to get rid of the ads, even if it doesn't come with the other benefits the subscription offers, then I'd consider redownloading. Until then, 2/5, and the second star is only for gameplay.

The game itself is definitely fun but the ad placement is AGRESSIVE. EVERYTIME you finish a level, everytime you die you get one. And then there is a recharge time for lives. Too many barriers to what would otherwise be a solid game. The arcade mode especially is frantic fun. Maybe the purchased game is more fun since it wouldn't have ads. Update: Even after purchase the ads are aggressive and there is still daily energy! Prevents it from getting 5 stars. But I would check out a sequel.
